--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 1916a287e7d4abf448f52361f3e8cb1c, type: 3}
  m_Name: Bad end
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::Dialog
  lines:
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: Yo, so a little birdie just told me you went after Ms Slitmouth herself
      by yourself.
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: "First, you are one insane bastard to take her on as your 2nd contract
      ever. Secondly, I\u2019m impressed you managed to take her down by yourself. "
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: " Most would\u2019ve had an extra member or 2 to back them up taking her
      on, but she always managed to slip away."
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: You
    line: Yeah, thanks-
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: "I\u2019m not done. While you did a good thing taking her down, your little
      scuffle caused a little collateral damage. "
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: "It\u2019s gonna be hard to cover this. So by all means, you kinda almost
      sort of did mess up."
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: But oh well. Anything you wanna say?
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: You
    line: 'Actually yeah. When I took her down, she seemed angry. '
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: You
    line: "I don\u2019t know whether I should feel good about exorcising her or feel
      guilty that I did it like that."
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: "Yeah I hear that. To be honest that\u2019s just the way it is. Most if
      not all spirits are tied to something that happened to them when they were
      alive. "
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: "Whether it\u2019s a past experience,"
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: 'a feeling when they died, or a certain person, if they carry that with
      them in death they are stuck here until they can move on. '
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: Exorcising them through combat is basically forcefully removing them from
      the world.
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: "It\u2019s okay to feel guilty about not being able to help them how you
      wanted. "
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: Supervisor
    line: "It\u2019s just part of the job."
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: You
    line: "...Yeah\u2026I guess you\u2019re right."
    SpriteRange: 0
  - speaker: You
    line: "Get some rest for the day. I\u2019ll check in with you later alright."
    SpriteRange: 0
  buttons: []
